<dl id="n12208b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12208b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12208b"> 208(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> smoke = beard of / the fire <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12208b"><li>FW 501.25 </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/lexrA.htm#n12208b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/rA/l39rA.htm#n12208b">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12208b">MS BL 47482b-84v</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:044 <a name="rA2d" href="../../ff/fdra/rda.htm#rA2d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/r/ra2d.htm#n12208b">Draft: III&sect;3A.2</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"> J&apos;ai ici un bouc; quand tu l&apos;attaches &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur d&apos;une maison, sa barbe trouve moyen de sortir &agrave; l&apos;ext&eacute;rieur, &mdash; Cela, c&apos;est le feu: quand tu <font color="green">[l&apos;]</font>allumes &agrave; l&apos;int&eacute;rieur d&apos;une maison, la fum&eacute;e sort &agrave; l&apos;ext&eacute;rieur. <br><font color="green">[(Riddle:) I have a nanny goat here; when you tie it up inside a house, its beard will find a way of getting outside. (Answer: a fire: when you light a fire inside a house, the smoke goes outside.]</font> <small> Maurice Delafosse, <a name="LNEG" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LNEG"><cite title="source">L'&acirc;me n&egrave;gre</cite></a> (1922) 172 (Riddles)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
